Avoid! What a monumental disappointment this new adaptation of "Snow White" is! Supposedly modern, the film is in reality nothing more than a confused collection of poorly digested ideas. The script, wanting at all costs to correct the tales of the past, falls into the trap of hyper-correction and empties the story of all its poetry and magic. The casting choices, especially for the Queen, cruelly lack the presence and credibility necessary to embody the "fairest of them all." The new songs are completely forgettable and break the rhythm of the story instead of enriching it. The visual effects, at times, are painful to watch and sadly recall a low-cost television series. It is a soulless, charmless version that betrays the spirit of the original tale without offering anything worthwhile in exchange. An hour and a half completely wasted.
